commit.message:
Correctly collapse multiple consecutive bindings.

As per the specification, if several bindings (".", "*") are following
each other, they are treated as if there was only a single binding,
wherein it is treated as "." if and only if all of the consecutive bindings
were tight ("."); otherwise, it is treated as a single loose ("*") binding.

fixes #79

Update version correctly.

We go straight to 1.2 because 1.1 has been released on Github already.

Merge pull request #72 from Airblader/bug-71

Parse entries with empty value correctly.

Parse entries with empty value correctly.

This patch fixes how an entry like

    some.component:

is parsed. Previously, this would error out and ignore the entry,
but the correct behavior is to parse it and assign the empty value
to it. This is needed for applications to differentiate between a
resource not being defined and it having an empty value.

fixes #71

Merge pull request #63 from psychon/xlib-deps

Add a hard dependency on Xlib

Add a hard dependency on Xlib

We could do lots of magic to only compare the test results against Xlib if Xlib
is available, but... why? Xlib isn't that much of an uncommon dependency.
Everyone can easily install it and the library libxcb-xrm.so does not depend on
it anyway.

Drop dependency on x11-xcb / Xlib-xcb.h

It's unused.

Merge pull request #61 from psychon/autoconf-xlib-checks

Autoconf xlib checks

Clean up linking of tests

Previously, some of the tests were linked against stuff that they didn't
actually use. This commit removes these libraries.

Additionally, this (silently (or not)) fixes a mistake of the previous commit
which accidentally made tests/database not link against xcb-aux even though it
uses xcb-aux.

Signed-off-by: Uli Schlachter <psychon@znc.in>

Signed-off-by: Uli Schlachter <uli.schlachter@informatik.uni-oldenburg.de>

Build tests conditionally

This moves the check for x11 and x11-xcb to configure.ac. The tests are only
enabled if the necessary libraries are found. Additionally, this commit adds
--enable-tests / --disable-tests flags to configure to forcefully disable tests
and, more important, to make configure fail if the dependencies for the tests
could not be found.

I hope someone can tell me a nicer way to implement this...

Fixes: https://github.com/Airblader/xcb-util-xrm/issues/60
